    • CanIBuyThisCard

      public boolean CanIBuyThisCard​(int idCard) throws CardNotFoundException
      method that checks if a player has enough resources to buy a card from the market and if the slots can store this card. The method expects a card that can be bought, and only handles the case where the card is not present in the market, not the case where the card is an illegal buy
      Parameters:
      idCard - card checked
      Returns:
      boolean true if the card can be bought, false otherwise
      Throws:
      CardNotFoundException - if the card does not exist in the market

    • availableSlotForCard

      public boolean availableSlotForCard​(int idCard) throws CardNotFoundException
      checks if a slot of this player can store the card selected
      Parameters:
      idCard - id of the card selected
      Returns:
      true if the card can be stored, false otherwise
      Throws:
      CardNotFoundException - the card selected does not exist in the market.
